
			
									<h5>Release Date: 14 December 2021</h5>
				
									Neo4j 4.3.8 is a maintenance release with many important improvements and fixes.
<h3>Highlights</h3>

<ul>
   <li>Update Log4j to 2.15.0 to address CVE-2021-44228</li>
   <li>CSV Import: add support for array data types point[], date[], time[], datetime[], localtime[], localdatetime[], duration[]</li>
   <li>neo4j stop now accepts â€“expand-commands</li>
   <li> Neo4j now also accepts datetime expressions including an offset of times immediately after switching from summer time to winter time.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Detailed Changes and Docs</h3>
For the complete list of all changes, please see <a href="https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j/wiki/Neo4j-4.3-changelog" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the changelog</a>.
Look for 4.3 Operations manual <a href="https://neo4j.com/docs/operations-manual/4.3/">here</a>.				
					